WEBVTT

00:03.481 --> 00:08.269
-Next case, The City of New York
vs. Captain James T. Kush.

00:08.312 --> 00:10.227
He was arrested for growing
and selling marijuana

00:10.271 --> 00:11.881
on his charter boat.

00:11.924 --> 00:13.448
-Hold on.

00:13.491 --> 00:16.320
Yes, this is the least
surprised I've ever been.

00:16.364 --> 00:19.410
-Your Honor, my client
runs a respectable business

00:19.454 --> 00:23.327
beloved by college students,
Deadheads,

00:23.371 --> 00:26.243
and Woody Harrelson.

00:26.287 --> 00:30.421
-Plus, Your Excellency,
I was in international waters.

00:30.465 --> 00:34.338
My only judge should be the sea.

00:34.382 --> 00:36.862
-Um, you were in the East River.

00:36.906 --> 00:39.865
That's not international
or water.

00:39.909 --> 00:41.867
Still, though, felony
drug trafficking

00:41.911 --> 00:43.739
seems a little steep.

00:43.782 --> 00:46.437
Uh, Counselor, do you know why
the DA's office went so harsh?

00:46.481 --> 00:48.309
-Hmm? Oh, absolutely,

00:48.352 --> 00:50.963
I am listening.

00:51.007 --> 00:53.270
-The court chooses to let
the defendant off with a fine

00:53.314 --> 00:56.143
and a stern "don't ye be growin'
any more cannabis

00:56.186 --> 00:59.407
on yer vessel, argh."

00:59.450 --> 01:01.452
-Okay, dude,
a piece of advice --

01:01.496 --> 01:03.150
Cheetos are not a deodorant.

01:07.719 --> 01:09.330
-Olivia, you feeling okay?

01:09.373 --> 01:10.635
I mean, I know
you don't like being here,

01:10.679 --> 01:13.856
but tonight it actually shows.

01:13.899 --> 01:15.814
-It's hard to care
about these other cases

01:15.858 --> 01:17.555
when Eli Bettencourt
is over there.

01:17.599 --> 01:20.558
-Wait, Eli Bettencourt?
Is here? Tonight?

01:20.602 --> 01:23.692
Who is that?

01:23.735 --> 01:25.346
-He's the one with the nurse.

01:25.389 --> 01:27.435
He's one of the city's
biggest political power brokers.

01:27.478 --> 01:28.827
And luckily for me,
he was assaulted

01:28.871 --> 01:30.525
on his way home from dinner.

01:30.568 --> 01:32.353
If I win, I'll gain
his undying gratitude

01:32.396 --> 01:34.398
and be on my way to becoming
the first classically hot

01:34.442 --> 01:37.009
Supreme Court Justice.

01:37.053 --> 01:38.663
Well, u-unless you count
Earl Warren.

01:38.707 --> 01:40.752
-Ooh, he was a smoke show.

01:43.494 --> 01:46.715
-Now, if you'll excuse me,
destiny awaits.

01:48.847 --> 01:51.502
-Your Honor, District Attorney
Jeff Dewitt,

01:51.545 --> 01:53.374
representing New York City

01:53.417 --> 01:56.377
and my dear friend
Eli Bettencourt.

01:56.420 --> 01:58.030
I'll take it from here, Alicia.

02:00.903 --> 02:02.687
-Well, stay positive.

02:02.731 --> 02:05.908
Maybe the victim in your next
case is also a power broker.

02:09.303 --> 02:13.002
Or maybe that giant snake
will swallow you whole.

02:13.045 --> 02:14.351
You just never know.

02:14.395 --> 02:15.657
That's Night Court, baby.

02:15.700 --> 02:17.137
[ Laughs ]

02:17.180 --> 02:24.840
♪♪

02:24.883 --> 02:32.587
♪♪

02:32.630 --> 02:35.372
-Well, if it isn't
Dan Fielding.

02:37.983 --> 02:39.550
So the rumors are true.

02:39.594 --> 02:41.944
You're a public defender now?
-Jeff Dewitt.

02:41.987 --> 02:45.208
I heard you drowned
on the Lehman Brothers boat.

02:45.252 --> 02:48.124
-You wish.
They do women and children last.

02:50.170 --> 02:52.084
-You two friends?
-Former colleagues.

02:52.128 --> 02:53.564
Jeff and I go way back.

02:53.608 --> 02:55.218
I used to give him advice
on how to dress.

02:55.262 --> 02:58.569
Obviously he's forgotten
all of it.

02:58.613 --> 03:01.006
-I'm actually glad you're here,
Mr. District Attorney.

03:01.050 --> 03:02.921
I've noticed some trends
coming out of your office

03:02.965 --> 03:04.271
that I'd really like
to talk to you about.

03:04.314 --> 03:05.359
-Too much justice?

03:05.402 --> 03:08.579
Up top, boom!

03:08.623 --> 03:11.321
No, of course, the DA's office
takes the concerns

03:11.365 --> 03:13.454
of a jurist like yourself
very seriously.

03:13.497 --> 03:15.412
Let's -- Let's get a meeting
on the books.

03:15.456 --> 03:17.893
-Oh, I've never had a meeting
on the books.

03:17.936 --> 03:19.764
I've had a meeting about books.

03:19.808 --> 03:21.984
Back home when they tried to ban
"Cat in the Hat"

03:22.027 --> 03:23.638
for being pro-mischief.

03:26.423 --> 03:28.991
-Care to bet on the outcome
like in the old days, Dan?

03:29.034 --> 03:31.515
-Sadly I'm no longer
a gambling man.

03:31.559 --> 03:33.213
So say 500?

03:33.256 --> 03:35.563
-Easy money.
She looks like a pushover.

03:35.606 --> 03:39.043
-Ah, sweet Jeff, you're going
to wish you died at sea.

03:39.088 --> 03:41.003
-Next up, The People
vs. Gil Crandall.

03:41.046 --> 03:43.527
-My office is charging assault
and robbery in the first degree.

03:43.571 --> 03:45.094
-See, this is exactly

03:45.137 --> 03:46.922
the kind of excessive charge
I'm talking about.

03:46.965 --> 03:49.185
-The fact is Mr. Bettencourt
was attacked

03:49.228 --> 03:54.059
for his to-go container
of hard-earned oysters.

03:54.103 --> 03:59.804
Gil here stole food out of this
great man's beautiful mouth.

04:01.719 --> 04:04.200
-Well, according to
the doorman's statement --

04:04.244 --> 04:07.159
-Ooh, I wonder whose side
the doorman is going to be on.

04:07.203 --> 04:09.031
-The two men
bumped into each other

04:09.074 --> 04:11.816
and Mr. Bettencourt threw
his doggie bag at the defendant,

04:11.860 --> 04:14.471
yelling, "Suck on that, Poor-o."

04:16.560 --> 04:18.345
-By the way,
I'm a cashless business now.

04:18.387 --> 04:20.999
I have something called Venmo.

04:21.043 --> 04:23.175
♪♪

04:23.219 --> 04:24.960
What's all this?

04:25.003 --> 04:27.963
-Ah, I have a meeting tomorrow
afternoon with Jeff Dewitt

04:28.006 --> 04:30.313
at something called
the Manhattan Heritage Club.

04:30.357 --> 04:32.707
-Heritage Club?
That's old New York.

04:32.750 --> 04:35.710
You know, it was founded in 1784
as a place to be able

04:35.753 --> 04:39.496
to gossip behind
Alexander Hamilton's back.

04:39.540 --> 04:42.107
-Well, it sounds like the
perfect place to convince Jeff

04:42.151 --> 04:44.371
that his office's focus
on conviction rates

04:44.414 --> 04:47.374
is ruining lives and not
making the city any safer.

04:47.417 --> 04:49.506
-And you're going to say
all those words to him?

04:49.550 --> 04:50.986
-Of course not.

04:51.029 --> 04:53.771
I also have my iPad loaded up
with pie charts.

04:53.815 --> 04:56.296
Ooh, do you think
I should call it a pie pad?

04:59.603 --> 05:01.257
-Thank God I'm here.

05:03.520 --> 05:08.308
You know, if you tell him what
you want, you will never get it.

05:08.351 --> 05:12.312
You need Dan Fielding's
three-pronged approach

05:12.355 --> 05:14.792
to backroom dealing.

05:14.836 --> 05:18.492
Alright, you start with
a few good-natured insults,

05:18.535 --> 05:21.538
Follow it up with a couple
of backhanded compliments, huh?

05:21.582 --> 05:24.193
And by that time, he's going
to be three scotches deep

05:24.236 --> 05:26.630
and he will tell you
what he really wants

05:26.674 --> 05:28.589
and then you're
in the driver's seat.

05:28.632 --> 05:29.633
Metaphorically speaking.

05:29.677 --> 05:31.287
If you're actually in a car,

05:31.331 --> 05:34.769
it's a whole different
set of prongs.

05:34.812 --> 05:37.511
-Dan, I appreciate the advice,
but I'm all good.

05:37.554 --> 05:39.426
This isn't some backroom deal.

05:39.469 --> 05:41.123
In fact, when I meet with Jeff,

05:41.166 --> 05:45.909
I'm going to ask for
the front-iest room they've got.

05:45.954 --> 05:47.869
-He's going to eat you alive.

05:53.701 --> 05:55.137
-Beef jerky?

05:55.180 --> 05:58.575
Why are you eating shame food
out in the open?

05:58.619 --> 06:01.186
-Eli was supposed to be
my Golden Ticket out of here.

06:01.230 --> 06:03.406
And then Jeff Dewitt showed up
like a fat German kid

06:03.450 --> 06:05.365
and snatched
my Golden Ticket away.

06:07.845 --> 06:10.457
-Hey, it's still a win,
as long as you're not

06:10.500 --> 06:12.676
one of those
four weird grandparents

06:12.720 --> 06:16.550
sleeping head to toe
in the living room.

06:16.593 --> 06:18.203
Well, at least you don't have
to waste your Saturday

06:18.247 --> 06:21.424
at Jeff's dumb old club
like Abby.

06:21.468 --> 06:24.645
-Abby got invited to
the Manhattan Heritage Club?

06:24.688 --> 06:26.560
The premier club for
legal elites in New York City?

06:26.603 --> 06:29.693
The club that I have dreamed
of joining ever since I realized

06:29.737 --> 06:32.392
the pure joy
of excluding people?

06:32.435 --> 06:34.742
If I got there, I wouldn't
have to wait for some Eli

06:34.784 --> 06:36.308
to get punched in the face.

06:36.352 --> 06:39.268
That club is crawling with rich,
punchable old men.

06:39.311 --> 06:42.358
-Crawling? Is that what rich
people do when we're not around?

06:42.402 --> 06:46.144
Do you get so much money they're
like, "I'm a baby again"?

06:47.972 --> 06:50.540
-That place is wasted on Abby.
She doesn't want to use

06:50.584 --> 06:52.324
social interaction
to advance her career.

06:52.368 --> 06:54.588
She just wants to be friends
with people, like a psycho,

06:54.631 --> 06:58.853
and unironically use terms
like -- Lady date!

06:58.896 --> 07:02.900
I just never get tired
of calling it that.

07:02.944 --> 07:04.946
-I am so glad
we're finally doing this.

07:04.989 --> 07:06.251
Even if the only time
you had available

07:06.295 --> 07:07.731
was when I had to be
at this club.

07:07.775 --> 07:11.518
-Uh-huh, yeah, definitely here
just for you.

07:11.561 --> 07:13.302
-You could help me
talk that DA talk with Jeff

07:13.345 --> 07:16.218
and then we can scoot off
to Color Me Mine.

07:16.261 --> 07:17.915
-Color me excited.

07:22.006 --> 07:23.617
It's everything I ever dreamed.

07:23.660 --> 07:25.009
There's the state's attorney.

07:25.053 --> 07:27.621
Oh, and the governor's
chief of staff.

07:27.664 --> 07:29.492
And that sugar daddy husband
from "Real Housewives"

07:29.536 --> 07:31.886
whose name I always forget.
-Oh, it's Bradman.

07:31.929 --> 07:35.977
He got his neck done, but --
but that's not important.

07:36.020 --> 07:38.849
No, if we can get Jeff pumped
about evidence-based

07:38.893 --> 07:43.680
prosecution reform,
I really feel like -- Olivia?

07:43.724 --> 07:45.943
-Oh, you got this, girl.

07:45.987 --> 07:48.424
Oh! Is that a state
comptroller I see?

07:53.690 --> 07:56.693
-Judge Stone, welcome.

07:56.737 --> 07:58.129
What do you think
of our little club?

07:58.173 --> 08:00.784
-Ah, it's fancy.
I'll try to resist the urge

08:00.828 --> 08:02.917
to pull on all the books,
looking for a secret room.

08:02.960 --> 08:05.136
-Please do.

08:05.180 --> 08:07.661
Oh, and you'll never guess
who I ran into.

08:07.704 --> 08:09.271
-Judge Stone.

08:09.314 --> 08:11.795
As I live and breathe.

08:11.839 --> 08:14.581
Which makes me the
healthiest person in this room.

08:17.322 --> 08:19.237
-Dan, if I didn't know better,

08:19.281 --> 08:21.109
I would think you were
checking up on me.

08:21.152 --> 08:23.894
-Not at all. I've been a member
of this club since the '90s.

08:23.938 --> 08:26.331
And I am currently up to date
on my dues,

08:26.375 --> 08:29.596
despite what is clearly
a clerical error!

08:30.945 --> 08:32.729
-Well, strap in, Jeff.

08:32.773 --> 08:34.948
I am about to take you
on an epic journey

08:34.991 --> 08:36.341
to a safer New York.

08:36.385 --> 08:39.823
My iPad will be
our magic carpet as we --

08:39.866 --> 08:41.172
Oh, it seems that someone

08:41.216 --> 08:44.524
snatched our magic carpet
on the subway.

08:44.567 --> 08:47.439
-You think someone made off
with your iPad?

08:47.483 --> 08:49.529
Jeff, "made off," too soon?
[Madoff]

08:54.838 --> 08:56.057
Gentle ribbing.

08:56.100 --> 08:57.493
Prong one.

08:57.537 --> 08:59.364
Ch-Check.

08:59.408 --> 09:01.758
♪♪

09:01.802 --> 09:04.413
-Sorry to drag you down here
on your weekend, Gurgs.

09:04.456 --> 09:08.591
-Well, make it quick. Saturdays
are when I work on my novel.

09:08.635 --> 09:10.462
I just got to the twist.

09:10.506 --> 09:13.814
They were on a submarine
the whole time!

09:13.857 --> 09:15.859
-Whoa!

09:15.903 --> 09:17.992
-And there's a character
based on you.

09:18.035 --> 09:21.299
-What?
-But he dies like right away.

09:21.343 --> 09:22.823
Or does he?

09:22.866 --> 09:23.998
He does!

09:24.041 --> 09:26.957
[ Laughs ]

09:27.001 --> 09:29.351
So, what's Abby got you doing?

09:29.394 --> 09:31.179
-She wanted me to pick up
copies of her research

09:31.222 --> 09:33.355
to take to some snooty club.

09:33.398 --> 09:34.574
If they'll even let me in.

09:34.617 --> 09:36.140
-Alright, Neil,

09:36.184 --> 09:38.969
I'm tired of watching you
mope around about Abby.

09:39.013 --> 09:40.580
She's your boss
and she's engaged.

09:40.623 --> 09:42.016
It's not going to happen.

09:42.059 --> 09:45.236
But if you want to stand
a chance with any woman,

09:45.280 --> 09:46.760
you know what you need to do?

09:46.803 --> 09:48.631
-Hope your book gets big
and people recognize me

09:48.675 --> 09:51.415
as the cool guy
that dies in the beginning?

09:51.460 --> 09:54.158
-I didn't say cool.

09:54.202 --> 09:56.378
You need to build up
some confidence.

09:56.421 --> 09:57.509
Change your clothes, Neil.

09:57.553 --> 09:59.250
We're going clubbing.

09:59.294 --> 10:02.123
-Can I still wear comfy shoes?
-No, you may not.

10:07.258 --> 10:08.520
-Okay, my
presentation materials

10:08.564 --> 10:09.870
are running a little bit late,

10:09.913 --> 10:11.872
but I think
we should just dive in.

10:11.915 --> 10:13.613
My first slide was a word cloud

10:13.656 --> 10:15.397
which I will now describe
from memory.

10:15.440 --> 10:17.051
[ Cellphone ringtone playing ]

10:17.094 --> 10:19.227
-Oh, sorry, I got to take this.

10:19.270 --> 10:20.750
Hold on!

10:20.794 --> 10:22.012
It's my investment guy.

10:22.056 --> 10:24.058
If I don't answer,
he goes rogue.

10:24.101 --> 10:27.975
Last time, he went all in on
Theranos after the documentary.

10:28.018 --> 10:29.672
What?!

10:29.716 --> 10:31.021
-Hurry back.
I'll get us some steaks,

10:31.065 --> 10:32.675
a couple scotches.
-Oh, I can't.

10:32.719 --> 10:35.025
I'm seeing a nurse. She's got me
down to two steaks a day.

10:36.679 --> 10:39.464
-Dan, what are you doing?
I told you I got this.

10:39.508 --> 10:41.728
-Yes, I know.
No, I'm just helping.

10:41.771 --> 10:44.165
Look, these guys are trickier
than the cow tippers

10:44.208 --> 10:47.124
and Jet-Ski hooligans
you dealt with upstate.

10:47.168 --> 10:49.518
-We have some tough customers
back home.

10:49.561 --> 10:52.608
Biff Cratchit, Wink Honeycrisp,
Colonel Ciderman.

10:52.652 --> 10:54.479
-Okay, fine, fine, fine,
I don't need a rundown

10:54.523 --> 10:56.612
of the corn crime all-stars.

10:56.656 --> 10:58.440
I've known this guy for 30 years

10:58.483 --> 11:00.050
and you're not going to get
any traction with him

11:00.094 --> 11:03.140
until you figure out
what it is he wants from you.

11:03.184 --> 11:05.665
-I don't know. I think
I could sell him on this.

11:05.708 --> 11:07.318
People can change.
You changed.

11:07.362 --> 11:09.364
-Yeah, but I'm incredible.

11:11.366 --> 11:15.413
-Well, we're
sticking with coal!

11:15.457 --> 11:18.982
-Jeff, I think word clouds
can be a little abstract.

11:19.026 --> 11:20.462
Let's get concrete.

11:20.505 --> 11:22.594
Your policies
affect real people.

11:22.638 --> 11:24.161
-You know what, though, Abby,
I think, you know,

11:24.205 --> 11:26.337
maybe our friend
would rather talk

11:26.381 --> 11:28.949
about how you could
fast-track his cases

11:28.992 --> 11:32.213
or go easy on his buddies,
huh, huh, huh?

11:32.256 --> 11:35.303
Get him a restraining order
against all children.

11:38.262 --> 11:40.177
Are you winking
at any of these, Jeff?

11:40.221 --> 11:43.964
-Actually, I'm not into
horse trading anymore.

11:44.007 --> 11:47.097
Unless you have an actual
horse you -- you want to trade.

11:47.141 --> 11:50.535
I have got one I am dying
to get rid of.

11:50.579 --> 11:53.800
-So, no meat, no horse trading.

11:53.843 --> 11:55.889
You've changed.

11:55.932 --> 11:57.717
-That's interesting.

11:57.760 --> 11:59.283
Dan, should we get
something to eat?

11:59.327 --> 12:01.372
I hear the crow here
is excellent.

12:01.416 --> 12:05.202
-It is. They call it field squab
and it is to die for.

12:05.246 --> 12:06.943
Field squab!

12:06.987 --> 12:10.164
♪♪

12:10.207 --> 12:11.861
-I can't believe you wore that.

12:11.905 --> 12:15.647
You look like an off-Strip
blackjack dealer.

12:15.691 --> 12:18.694
-Uh, I saw a guy dressed
like this in the Olympics.

12:18.738 --> 12:21.610
Granted, he was wearing
ice skates.

12:21.653 --> 12:23.960
I don't know, Gurgs. Let's just
leave the folder and go.

12:24.004 --> 12:27.398
-No. You need this
and you belong here.

12:27.442 --> 12:29.139
Remember what Tony Robbins says.

12:29.183 --> 12:31.751
-"Get out of my seminar, Neil,
you're bumming us out"?

12:31.794 --> 12:34.057
-Exactly, and we're going
to prove him wrong.

12:34.101 --> 12:35.406
Just follow me.

12:35.450 --> 12:37.931
The finest of afternoons.

12:37.974 --> 12:40.803
We're here to see -- Arthur!

12:40.847 --> 12:43.632
Arthur, is that you, old boy?

12:43.675 --> 12:45.329
They told me you was there.

12:48.289 --> 12:50.552
-I belong here.

12:50.595 --> 12:53.381
-Of course you do.

12:53.424 --> 12:55.513
Spa waters, table three.

12:55.557 --> 12:56.863
And put on a tie.

12:56.906 --> 12:58.516
No one wants to see your neck.

13:05.785 --> 13:08.526
-I-I just think I could
really thrive in this club.

13:08.570 --> 13:11.791
All I need is someone
to sponsor my membership.

13:11.834 --> 13:15.533
-Sorry, miss, I already
gave my one sponsorship

13:15.577 --> 13:17.318
to my youngest son here.

13:24.107 --> 13:27.023
-Well, I'll leave you
to your mush.

13:30.244 --> 13:32.202
-I keep all my club
clothes at work.

13:32.246 --> 13:35.336
Trials end, I throw this on,
show up at a club,

13:35.379 --> 13:38.078
and sometimes the deejay hasn't
even gotten to the drop yet.

13:38.121 --> 13:41.908
Everyone's waiting around like,
mm, mm, mm, mm, mm, mm,

13:41.951 --> 13:45.433
and then I show up and it's like
bwoooo, wah-wah-wah-wah!

13:45.476 --> 13:47.827
[ Laughs ]

13:47.870 --> 13:50.830
Olivia, what are you doing here?

13:50.873 --> 13:52.614
-What am I doing here?

13:52.657 --> 13:54.529
I capitalized on a woman's
desperate need for friendship.

13:54.572 --> 13:56.270
What are you doing here?

13:56.313 --> 13:58.794
-Oh, I was just teaching Neil
a lesson in confidence.

13:58.838 --> 14:00.230
-Neil's here?

14:00.274 --> 14:03.930
What, they just let anyone
in this dump?

14:03.973 --> 14:05.192
-And that's the amount
of recidivism

14:05.235 --> 14:06.671
reduced by this approach.

14:06.715 --> 14:08.108
Now, here's the point
in the presentation

14:08.151 --> 14:09.805
where I would've offered you
whipped cream

14:09.849 --> 14:12.547
to go with your pie chart,
and you would've loved it.

14:12.590 --> 14:15.811
-Well, I got to tell you,
this has been eye-opening.

14:15.855 --> 14:18.640
-Excuse me.

14:18.683 --> 14:20.424
Oh, good, someone found my iPad.

14:20.468 --> 14:21.817
And all I need to do
to get it back

14:21.861 --> 14:24.298
is answer a series of riddles.

14:24.341 --> 14:27.344
Excuse me.

14:27.388 --> 14:28.650
-So, Jeff,
you're actually interested

14:28.693 --> 14:30.130
in what Abby is saying?

14:30.173 --> 14:32.741
-Oh, I'm eating this up.

14:32.784 --> 14:34.351
Usually I have to bribe a nanny

14:34.395 --> 14:36.527
to figure out
a target's weaknesses.

14:36.571 --> 14:40.705
But she is handing me
all the material I need.

14:40.749 --> 14:44.013
-Need to improve society?

14:44.057 --> 14:46.189
-[ Laughing ]

14:50.802 --> 14:53.501
No.

14:53.544 --> 14:55.982
To improve my chances
of getting re-elected.

14:56.025 --> 14:57.722
I've been looking for
a soft-on-crime judge

14:57.766 --> 15:00.073
to be the face of everything
destroying New York City,

15:00.116 --> 15:04.381
and she is
the perfect scapegoat.

15:04.425 --> 15:08.081
-Third scotch, third prong,
system works.

15:13.782 --> 15:16.045
-Abby, the third scotch worked.

15:16.089 --> 15:18.134
He wants a scapegoat
for the next election

15:18.178 --> 15:20.093
and it's going to be you.

15:20.136 --> 15:21.398
So now we know what he wants.

15:21.442 --> 15:22.834
We can use it against him.

15:22.878 --> 15:24.314
-I don't want any
more prongs, Dan.

15:24.358 --> 15:25.968
-No, no, no, no, no,
we're done with prongs.

15:26.012 --> 15:27.100
We're into phases.

15:27.143 --> 15:29.537
Now, phase one has five prongs.

15:29.580 --> 15:31.626
-Dan, stop it.
I want to change things

15:31.669 --> 15:33.367
and I'm not going to do that
by playing the same games

15:33.410 --> 15:36.283
you've all been playing
since the wall-deer had bodies.

15:36.326 --> 15:37.762
-I don't want you to get hurt.

15:37.806 --> 15:40.591
-Thank you, but I got this.

15:40.635 --> 15:42.637
I want to do things my way.

15:42.680 --> 15:45.118
-I understand.
Enjoy your Shirley Temple.

15:45.161 --> 15:46.554
-Sherlock Temple.

15:46.597 --> 15:50.427
They don't have drinks
named after women.

15:50.471 --> 15:54.388
-That's why I haven't
paid my dues.

15:54.431 --> 15:56.781
You should all be ashamed
of yourselves.

15:59.871 --> 16:02.613
-Rough day?
-Yeah, it's been --

16:02.657 --> 16:03.745
Neil, what is happening?

16:03.788 --> 16:05.486
Why are you bartending?

16:05.529 --> 16:06.748
-Well, I came to bring you
that folder,

16:06.791 --> 16:08.576
which I'm realizing I never did.

16:08.619 --> 16:11.796
They thought I was a waiter,
so I said, "This isn't my job,"

16:11.840 --> 16:14.756
confidently, and they
promoted me to bartender.

16:14.799 --> 16:16.584
It's actually
very fulfilling work.

16:16.627 --> 16:17.889
People want my attention.

16:17.933 --> 16:20.370
They ask for my advice.
It's nice.

16:20.414 --> 16:23.547
So care to pour me a story?

16:25.288 --> 16:28.074
-Just things seemed so much
simpler upstate.

16:28.117 --> 16:31.164
People here seem
to have an agenda.

16:31.207 --> 16:33.470
-I've lived a lot
of lives today.

16:33.514 --> 16:34.776
And if there's one thing
I've learned,

16:34.819 --> 16:38.258
it's that people
are the same everywhere.

16:38.301 --> 16:41.174
Some are just lousy tippers.

16:41.217 --> 16:45.178
-Wow, Neil,
that's really profound.

16:45.221 --> 16:48.224
[ Loud jingling ]

16:48.268 --> 16:51.010
That ice is really loud!

16:51.053 --> 16:52.794
-Oh, I don't know
where the ice is.

16:52.837 --> 16:56.972
I just put my keys in here
and I shake them up for show.

16:57.016 --> 16:59.409
If someone wants a cocktail,
I just recommend a scotch.

16:59.453 --> 17:01.020
[ Chuckles ]

17:01.063 --> 17:04.545
I tell them "it's peaty."

17:04.588 --> 17:07.374
-Peaty.
-It means smoky.

17:07.416 --> 17:08.505
Look, it's Scottish swamp juice.

17:08.549 --> 17:10.637
I don't know why people like it.

17:10.681 --> 17:11.813
-Petey -- That's it.

17:11.856 --> 17:14.294
Jeff is a corn crime all-star.

17:14.337 --> 17:16.773
And I know just the person
who can help me prove it.

17:16.818 --> 17:19.386
-Eh, not going to help you.

17:19.429 --> 17:21.866
-Can you just tell me if my
suspicions about Jeff are right?

17:21.910 --> 17:24.694
-Uh, no,
because if they are true,

17:24.739 --> 17:28.047
maybe I confront Jeff
and he gets me into this club.

17:28.089 --> 17:29.831
-Why do you want to be a part
of this club anyway?

17:29.874 --> 17:31.006
You're better than this place.

17:31.050 --> 17:32.529
-You think I don't know that?

17:32.573 --> 17:34.270
I hate this place
and everything it stands for.

17:34.314 --> 17:36.055
The people are jerks,
it smells like gravy,

17:36.098 --> 17:37.621
and eight different men
came up to me

17:37.665 --> 17:39.884
and asked me who my husband
told me to vote for.

17:42.670 --> 17:45.542
If you want to get ahead,
this is where you have to be.

17:45.586 --> 17:48.763
-Blackmailing Jeff to get into
this club is not the dream.

17:48.806 --> 17:50.895
You using your drive
and intelligence

17:50.939 --> 17:53.333
to rise to a position of power
where all the Jeffs

17:53.376 --> 17:56.858
wants to blackmail you,
that's the real dream.

17:56.901 --> 17:58.599
-You really think
that could happen for me?

17:58.642 --> 18:01.863
-Stick with me and one day
people will be lining up

18:01.906 --> 18:03.560
to ruin your life.

18:06.563 --> 18:08.609
Alright, Jeff Dewitt,
let's talk!

18:08.652 --> 18:10.176
Damn it, why'd that
have to be a curtain?

18:10.219 --> 18:11.568
I just feel like I just stormed
into a shower.

18:11.612 --> 18:13.396
-No, it worked.
Keep going.

18:15.790 --> 18:19.054
-Let me tell you about a little
scandal that happened upstate.

18:19.098 --> 18:21.709
You see, Biff Cratchit always
won the Squash Art

18:21.752 --> 18:23.754
competition at the county fair,
but that's only because

18:23.798 --> 18:26.496
Petey Gooster always gave him
his best squash every year.

18:26.540 --> 18:28.672
But the year that Biff
finally lost was the year

18:28.716 --> 18:31.501
that Petey found out that
Biff was sleeping with his wife.

18:31.545 --> 18:35.288
After that, Biff never
won anything ever again.

18:35.331 --> 18:38.508
-Well, I like a carnival sex
yarn as much as the next man.

18:38.552 --> 18:42.469
But what the hell does any
of that have to do with me?

18:42.512 --> 18:45.254
-You let it slip earlier
that you're dating a nurse.

18:45.298 --> 18:46.734
And in court the other day,

18:46.777 --> 18:50.216
I saw you making
a flirty face at Eli's nurse,

18:50.259 --> 18:52.435
who I also learned is his wife.

18:52.479 --> 18:55.134
-And his daughter's
former roommate.

18:55.177 --> 18:58.093
Gross.

18:58.137 --> 18:59.529
-I think you're having
an affair

18:59.573 --> 19:01.662
with your biggest campaign
donor's wife.

19:01.705 --> 19:03.185
And if that comes out,
just like old Biff,

19:03.229 --> 19:04.926
you're going to lose
your squash daddy,

19:04.969 --> 19:08.582
and that squash for you
is 800K every election cycle.

19:08.625 --> 19:10.236
-Nice story.

19:10.279 --> 19:11.802
You can't prove it.

19:11.846 --> 19:14.370
-Ooh, but I can.

19:14.414 --> 19:16.851
Remember that Eli Bettencourt
case you stole from me?

19:16.894 --> 19:18.548
Well, I called every witness,

19:18.592 --> 19:21.595
but his wife wasn't one of them
because she was here.

19:21.638 --> 19:23.292
"With a friend."

19:23.336 --> 19:25.381
-A friend that Neil's
new co-workers

19:25.425 --> 19:28.428
at a job he doesn't really have
confirmed was you.

19:28.471 --> 19:31.518
And I heard that you two were
in a back room doing face stuff.

19:31.561 --> 19:32.606
-Just say kissing.

19:32.649 --> 19:34.651
-Got it.

19:34.695 --> 19:38.438
-Well, that is a large pile
of dirt you have there.

19:38.481 --> 19:39.787
What do you want?

19:39.830 --> 19:42.224
-Oh, same thing
I've always wanted.

19:42.268 --> 19:44.966
For you to take
this research to heart

19:45.009 --> 19:47.621
and effect some positive change.

19:47.664 --> 19:49.666
-I don't know what your game is.

19:49.710 --> 19:51.451
-No game. Games are your thing.

19:51.494 --> 19:53.801
I'm just sharing information.

19:53.844 --> 19:55.672
-So am I being blackmailed
or not?!

19:55.716 --> 19:59.241
This is really unnerving!

19:59.285 --> 20:01.374
I'm going to read
the whole thing, I promise!

20:01.417 --> 20:05.247
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey, hey,
so, are -- are -- are we cool?

20:05.291 --> 20:07.206
-Oh, and, um,
you guys might want to find

20:07.249 --> 20:08.685
a different place to hang out.

20:08.729 --> 20:10.948
Yeah, turns out that
this club is in violation

20:10.992 --> 20:12.602
of all kinds
of different codes,

20:12.646 --> 20:15.779
so expect a fun little visit
from people in jackets.

20:15.823 --> 20:17.607
[ Laughs ]

20:17.651 --> 20:19.696
-Up top, boom!
-Up top, boom!

20:21.176 --> 20:24.484
♪♪

20:24.527 --> 20:26.268
-Turns out
I'm much more comfortable

20:26.312 --> 20:30.707
in a place where I am by far
the most successful person.

20:30.751 --> 20:33.971
-So, you decided to go
with blackmail after all?

20:34.015 --> 20:36.060
-Absolutely not.
He just thought I did

20:36.104 --> 20:38.149
because that's
how he does things.

20:38.193 --> 20:40.630
And as you said,
he hasn't changed in 30 years.

20:40.674 --> 20:44.199
-You know why?
-Because he's not incredible?

20:44.243 --> 20:47.202
-Well, yeah, but

20:47.246 --> 20:49.900
also he doesn't have anyone

20:49.944 --> 20:52.903
in his life to make him better.

20:52.947 --> 20:57.038
Like my late wife
or your father.

20:57.081 --> 21:00.563
Or you.

21:00.607 --> 21:03.044
-Cocktail, m'lady?
-No, thank you.

21:03.087 --> 21:05.786
I don't drink.
-Neat.

21:10.269 --> 21:13.272
So glad I spent $600
on bartending stuff.

21:15.404 --> 21:18.494
[ Key clinks ]

21:18.538 --> 21:20.583
-Why does this drink
have a key in it?
